properties.NAME: Alabama
properties.CHANGE: MARION's overlap of the state of Mississippi and TUSCALOOSA's overlap of the state of Mississippi ended.

properties.NAME: Arkansas Territory
properties.CHANGE: CLARK, CRAWFORD, LOVELEY, and MILLER lost to Indian lands when the treaty between the United States and Cherokee Indians established the western line of Arkansas Territory north of Red River along the eastern line of the Choctaw Cession.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 7, p. 311; Gabler, 37-39; Royce, 720-721; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Connecticut
properties.CHANGE: HARTFORD lost part of the town of Southwick (the "Southwick Jog") to HAMPSHIRE (Mass.) when the state boundary was adjusted.

properties.NAME: District of Columbia
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed district from land ceded by Maryland and Virginia to be the seat of national government.

properties.NAME: Delaware
properties.CHANGE: The three Lower Counties, of KENT, NEW CASTLE, and SUSSEX became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The name Delaware was formally adopted on 20 September 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Florida Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created the Territory of Florida from the provinces of East and West Florida ceded by Spain to the United States. The territory had the same boundaries as the present state of Florida.

properties.NAME: Georgia
properties.CHANGE: Georgia ceded to the United States much of present Mississippi and Alabama. This area became unorganized federal territory and Georgia Western Lands were eliminated.

properties.NAME: Illinois
properties.CHANGE: The state of Illinois was created from Illinois Territory; Illinois Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Indiana
properties.CHANGE: The state of Indiana was created from Indiana Territory and small parts of Illinois and Michigan Territories.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 57 [1816], secs. 1-2/p. 289 and res. 1 [1816]/p. 399; Van Zandt, 115)

properties.NAME: Indian Territory
properties.CHANGE: Indian Territory gained from Arkansas Territory when the Treaty of Washington between the United States and Choctaw Indians definitively established the eastern line of the Choctaw Cession and affirmed Choctaw control of the area west of the line.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 7, p. 311; Gabler, 37-39; Royce, 720-721; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Kentucky
properties.CHANGE: The state of Kentucky was created from the Kentucky District of Virginia.

properties.NAME: Louisiana
properties.CHANGE: The State of Louisiana was created from Orleans Territory; Orleans Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: Maine was separated from Massachusetts and admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Maryland
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed district from land ceded by Maryland and Virginia to be the seat of national government.

properties.NAME: Maine
properties.CHANGE: Maine was separated from Massachusetts and admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Michigan Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Illinois was created from Illinois Territory. Michigan Territory gained the former parts of Illinois and Indiana Territories in present Wisconsin and the Upper Peninsula of present Michigan.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 10:803; U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 67 [1818], sec. 7/p. 431, and res. 1 [1818]/p. 536)

properties.NAME: Missouri
properties.CHANGE: The state of Missouri was created from Missouri Territory, with all modern boundaries, except for the northwestern corner of the present state, which became unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Mississippi
properties.CHANGE: Surveyors demarcated the southern segment of the Alabama-Mississippi line, fixing the end point ten miles east of the mouth of the Pascagoula River.

properties.NAME: North Carolina
properties.CHANGE: Congress accepted North Carolina's cession of its western lands (i.e. present Tennessee).

properties.NAME: New Hampshire
properties.CHANGE: New Hampshire became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: New Jersey
properties.CHANGE: New Jersey became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: New York
properties.CHANGE: New York became an independent state on 4 July 1776, and Vermont declared its independence from New York on 15 January 1777. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Ohio
properties.CHANGE: The state of Ohio was created from the Northwest Territory and Indiana Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Ind. Terr., Exec. Journal, 114-115; Pence and Armstrong, 218; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 40 [1802], secs. 1-3/pp. 173-174; Van Zandt, 112)

properties.NAME: Oregon Country
properties.CHANGE: Based on American exploration of the Northwest, the United States claimed the Oregon Country, an area west of the 1803 Louisiana Purchase that was not specifically defined.

properties.NAME: Pennsylvania
properties.CHANGE: Pennsylvania purchased from the federal government the Erie Triangle, a small area immediately north of Pennsylvania and west of New York, giving Pennsylvania an outlet to Lake Erie.

properties.NAME: Rhode Island
properties.CHANGE: Rhode Island became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: South Carolina
properties.CHANGE: South Carolina became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Tennessee
properties.CHANGE: The state of Tennessee was created from the Territory of the United States South of the River Ohio (Southwest Territory); Southwest Territory eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 1, ch. 47[1796], pp. 491-492; Folmsbee, Corlew, and Mitchell 110)

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The unorganized federal territory lost to the creation of Indian Territory.

properties.NAME: Virginia
properties.CHANGE: The state of Kentucky was created from the Kentucky District of Virginia.

properties.NAME: Vermont
properties.CHANGE: The state of Vermont was admitted to the Union. The boundary with New York was settled by a joint commission before statehood.
